climbs.name: Overhanging Nightmare
climbs.fa: Paul Roberts, Kevin Keith, Jack Kelly-Willis

content.description:
Short but Sweet. Climb the slab straight up to the roof, pull directly over the roof into the overhanging hand/finger crack, fire this section up to the wide crack and pull up over the bulge to slab by climbing to a two bolt anchor. 

  Variation: instead of pulling directly over the roof you can traverse out right to gain the ledge above the roof bumping your first crux down a little bit but still leaves you with the real crux above.
content.location: When you hike to this cliff it will land you directly at the start of the route. Directly below the large 7' roof. Two Bolts and Chains at the top to rap/top belay.

content.description: Two Routes on a massive boulder that sits up to the left as you cross the bridge heading towards the Dam Wall
